This is the README for pam_unix2
--------------------------------

pam_unix2 comes as one module: pam_unix2.so

For getting the passwd entries, it uses NSS from glibc >= 2.1. This module
can get password entries from secure NIS+ server and change local, NIS
and NIS+ passwords.

This module supports passwords with DES, bigcrypt, MD5 and blowfish
encryption.

For more information about the varios options, please read the
pam_unix2.8 manual page.

 Thorsten Kukuk <kukuk@suse.de>, 15. September 2006
